Q_DESC: Adhitya is a smart boy, who is fond of numbers. His visit to a hospital made him think about its queue-token method followed there. There were some missing tokens. Patients are seated in  random order.  The only way to find the next patient is to find the person with the minimum token number among all the token numbers avvailable with the pending patients.  Input: 1.  No of patients, N,  0<N<=100,     2. N integers, that represents the token number T.       0<T<=200   Help Adhitya to write a C program using functions to do this task.
